Author: Zoran Regvart <zoran@regvart.com>
Date:   Fri Mar 11 10:56:28 2022 +0100

    Configure TLS in the Kaniko Chains demo
    
    When using exported OpenShift registry, i.e. on CRC
    `default-route-openshift-image-registry.apps-crc.testing`, we need to
    configure `kaniko` to trust the ingress CA certificate.
    
    In order to do that the chains-ca-cert secret created in
    hacbs-contract/infra-deployments#6 is used and mounted to the
    `kaniko-chains` taks using a volume. This diverges from the default
    `kaniko-chains` task so we need to patch it with the volume and
    volumeMount.
    
    Given that the key holding the trusted certificates in the
    `chains-ca-cert` secret is `ca-certificates.crt` this matches one of the
    paths that golang would looks at when loading trusted CA certificates
    (`/etc/ssl/certs/ca-certificates.crt`), and this makes it nicely
    suitable for the mount point.
    
    Ref. https://issues.redhat.com/browse/HACBS-105

